  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Safe and secure trauma and non-trauma management for Gaza vulnerable people.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DCA with Ahli Arab Hospital (AAH) will support trauma and non-trauma patients by providing much needed surgeries for them. Regarding non-trauma patients AAH will target 800 cases that are on the waiting list of the Ministry of Health (MoH) and in need of elective surgeries either through Minimal Invasive Surgeries or by open abdomen. Selection of the beneficiaries will be based on the vulnerability of the patients and AAH capacity in cooperation with MOH. Regarding trauma patients, 200 cases will undergo 2-3 surgeries along the project. Therefore, the trauma management procedures will be 400 surgical procedures. Moreover, 200 injured patients will have, follow up services in the OPDs and physical therapy department for a year. The cases will be either orthopedic or general surgery related to the recent escalation in Gaza. Criteria of vulnerability will be defined in a participatory manner with MoH, cluster level and partners. 

Furthermore, DCA will build the capacity of 30 of AAH technical team through Augusta Victoria in IPC. Augusta Victoria who is DCA&#x2019;s partner will conduct 3 visits throughout the project cycle and provide assistance to AAH in IPC and other needs.</narrative>
  </description>
